{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2831e9fb-10e3-4cb3-9892-55cb88a8b9bd","content":"Yes, you'll run into **framework compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 dropped support for end-of-life TFMs. Here's the breakdown:\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped (minimum is `net6.0`) |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped (minimum is `net6.0`) |\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to:**\n\n1. Replace `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` with supported TFMs like `net6.0` or `net8.0`.\n2. Update the packages — MSTest v3 also offers a single unified `MSTest` package instead of separate `TestFramework`/`TestAdapter` references.\n\n**Other MSTest v3 breaking changes to watch for:**\n- Some assert APIs and attributes have been tightened or removed.\n- `DeploymentItem` behavior changed.\n- Class/assembly cleanup defaults may differ.\n\nWould you like me to go ahead and update the project file for the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8804dda6-7221-45ad-9f27-4b91b44a8714","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a project targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nMSTest v3 has some important compatibility changes:\n\n1. **Minimum supported frameworks**: MSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Specifically:\n   - `.NET 5.0` is no longer supported (it's end-of-life). MSTest v3 requires at least .NET 6.0 for modern .NET.\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` is also no longer supported (end-of-life). MSTest v3 requires at least .NET 6.0.\n   - `.NET Framework 4.6.2` is still supported, so that target framework should work fine.\n\nSo the migration will require updating the project to target `net6.0` or later instead of `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1`, while the `net462` target can remain unchanged.\n\nMSTest v3 also consolidates the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages into a single `MSTest` meta-package, though the individual packages are still available. There are some breaking API changes to be aware of, but the main compatibility issue is the target framework requirement.","outputTokens":690,"requestId":"0839:5FAF2:82B4953:91AA970:69EAD523"},"id":"dc66e8c0-3687-49e2-ac7f-44bb45ab2a8f","timestamp":"2026-04-24T02:28:03.671Z","parentId":"53b64d63-6f5c-42df-b95d-707547745913"}
